        Education
      </h3>
      <p id="education">
        I've gotten around; first at Pennsylvania College of Technology for a
        Welding Certificate, now I'm finishing up a degree through Arizona State
        University studying Software Engineering. I pursued welding out of high
        school like any other high school kid, I didn't know any better and
        thought my Guidance Counselor knew more than I did about what I wanted
        to do with my life. If you can tell where this is going, I won't bore
        you with the details. To make a long story short I left in 2016, barely
        missing an Associates (by only two classes) and settled for a
        Certificate because I needed to move on. <br /><br />

        I knew I wanted to be an engineer because I loved numbers and had the
        right mindset for it, but wasn't sure what type I should pursue. I
        switched between Mechanical, Aerospace, and Software, and eventually
        settled on Software because I had tried programming and I've always had
        an interest in computers. So in the Fall of 2016 I started with Arizona
        State online and the rest is -as they say- history.
