    <section>
      <h3>
        Goals/Dreams
      </h3>
      <p>
        These days I'm more interested in getting out of the rat race than
        getting in. I've always been somewhat driven by money, understanding the
        necessity in our current society. I've spent a <i>LOT</i> of time
        thinking about how I want to spend my life, and most of the goals that
        I've found are simply unattainable with a traditional 9-5 job. For that
        reason, my main goal right now is to become financially independent.
        This means creating wealth and abandoning the cultural norms of 'work
        too much -> retire too late -> suffer due to high prices and low
        savings'. <br /><br />

        I dream of a society where money is unecessary, and for some people
        that's hard to understand. We've been indoctrinated by a culture that
        revolves around the financial obsession. We all know in our hearts that
        our culture is unsustainable, and the capitalist society creates wealth
        through greed, waste, and exploitation. I believe in a society where all
        people are equal, and there is no need for all of us to work jobs we
        hate for meager pay and bad benefits.
      </p>
    </section>

