        all of the national parks. I love nature and travelling, and I hope that I can use 
        my wealth and time to convert a school bus into a mobile home and go where I want 
        to when I want to. I also want to see other countries, mainly in Europe, but I 
        feel a spiritual connection to the Far Eastern countries as well, and I think it 
        would be incredible to see the temples in China and Japan. I don't plan to spend 
        all my time travelling, and when I'm at my 'home base', I want to focus on starting
        other enterprises. Some of those include; recycling, farming (livestock and greenery), 
        gaming (software and hardware). I want to give back to the world, and something I'm very 
        passionate about is food. I beleive every person deserves high quality, healthy food at 
        affordable prices. One of my first enterprises will likely be a farm to the likes of 
        Joel Salatin, with management intensive grazing producing the healthiest animals while 
        regenerating the land. I'm also inspired by the Eden Project, the worlds largest greenhouse 
        in Cornwall, UK. I would love to replicate something like that in the US, where I can build 
        a massive greenhouse to grow an ecosystem that doesn't normally thrive in my climate. I 
        believe in permaculture and perennials over the monoculture mindset that our system has 
        built and works very hard to maintain. 
      </p>
